Deep dive in Dockerfile:
https://rock-it.pl/how-to-write-excellent-dockerfiles/

Dockerfile Example:

FROM ubuntu

ADD . /app

RUN apt-get update \
	&& apt-get upgrade -y nodejs \
	&& apt-get install -y nodejs ssh mysql \
	&& cd /app && npm install

# this should start three processes, mysql and ssh
# in the background and node app in foreground
# isn't it beautifully terrible? <3
CMD mysql & sshd & npm start


Docker Compose:
https://docs.docker.com/compose/


Executing Python Scripts:

./<script-name>.py 

./<script-name>.py 2 3 4 

$0: <script-name>.py 
$1: 2
$2: 3
$3: 4


Important:

docker run : used to create a container 
docker build : used to create an image


